{"questionId":"16448718","questionHtml":"<p>Find the total distance that the particle travels in the first&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi></math>&nbsp;seconds.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>recognizing that integral of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;is required&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mn>0</mn><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>73</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></msubsup><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mi>v</mi><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>t</mi></math>&nbsp;</strong></em>OR<em><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mn>0</mn><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>73</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></msubsup><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mi>s</mi><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>t</mi></math>&nbsp;</strong></em>OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mn>0</mn><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>73</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></msubsup><mi>v</mi><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mn>0</mn><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>73</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></msubsup><mi>v</mi><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>t</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>:&nbsp;Only accept&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mn>0</mn><mi>q</mi></msubsup><mi>v</mi><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;if&nbsp;their value of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi></math>&nbsp;does not result in the particle changing direction in the first&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi></math>&nbsp;seconds.</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>68302</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>68</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>recognition that total distance travelled is the difference between the initial displacement and the displacement at minimum&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>initial displacement is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>38302</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp;AND at minimum is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em>&nbsp;<br>total distance travelled&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>38302</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>68302</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>68</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[3 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"16448718","referenceCode":"23N.2.SL.TZ2.5b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the total distance that the particle travels in the first q seconds.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 0]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.9—Kinematics problems","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.3—Graphing"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}